answer_cot:
Let $\omega = e^{2 \pi i/14}.$  We can identify $A$ with $2,$ $B$ with $-2,$ and $C_k$ with the complex number $2 \omega^k.$

[asy]
unitsize (3 cm);

int i;
pair A, B;
pair[] C;

A = (1,0);
B = (-1,0);
C[1] = dir(1*180/7);
C[2] = dir(2*180/7);
C[3] = dir(3*180/7);
C[4] = dir(4*180/7);
C[5] = dir(5*180/7);
C[6] = dir(6*180/7);

